</node>
<node id="FastAPI">
  <data key="d0">FastAPI</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">FastAPI is a modern web framework for building APIs with Python.&lt;SEP&gt;FastAPI is a web framework used in the API layer of the Portfolio Vault RAG.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0b9224c433c7a1dffba033eb8ed5c941&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-69b74b852f9cabc07d214d1a2ef1a1b7</data>
  <data key="d4">82ac66a6-7ad1-4828-936f-0374dc2f36fc&lt;SEP&gt;b603e4fb-1b99-49a2-b06a-0160ff173be3</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863738</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Pydantic Settings">
  <data key="d0">Pydantic Settings</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Pydantic Settings is an extension of Pydantic aimed at managing application settings and configurations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0b9224c433c7a1dffba033eb8ed5c941</data>
  <data key="d4">82ac66a6-7ad1-4828-936f-0374dc2f36fc</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863202</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Anthropic">
  <data key="d0">Anthropic</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Anthropic provides AI safety and research tools.&lt;SEP&gt;Anthropic is an organization providing models for text generation in the described application.&lt;SEP&gt;Anthropic, alongside OpenAI, provides token count data for cost computation in generation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0b9224c433c7a1dffba033eb8ed5c941&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d8787c2876f2fa9c466edf1494e57b95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9b2357e61536898e16b9f8b1b5949ab3</data>
  <data key="d4">82ac66a6-7ad1-4828-936f-0374dc2f36fc&lt;SEP&gt;b603e4fb-1b99-49a2-b06a-0160ff173be3</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863776</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="SQLModel">
  <data key="d0">SQLModel</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">SQLModel is a library for interacting with SQL databases from Python code.&lt;SEP&gt;SQLModel is the ORM tool used with PostgreSQL, facilitating table definitions and asynchronous operations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0b9224c433c7a1dffba033eb8ed5c941&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-69b74b852f9cabc07d214d1a2ef1a1b7</data>
  <data key="d4">82ac66a6-7ad1-4828-936f-0374dc2f36fc&lt;SEP&gt;b603e4fb-1b99-49a2-b06a-0160ff173be3</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863740</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Uvicorn">
  <data key="d0">Uvicorn</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">Uvicorn is a lightning-fast ASGI server implementation, using uvloop and httptools.&lt;SEP&gt;Uvicorn is a software server used to run the app and make APIs accessible.&lt;SEP&gt;Uvicorn is a combination with FastAPI in the API layer of Portfolio Vault RAG.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0b9224c433c7a1dffba033eb8ed5c941&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-69b74b852f9cabc07d214d1a2ef1a1b7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d8787c2876f2fa9c466edf1494e57b95</data>
  <data key="d4">82ac66a6-7ad1-4828-936f-0374dc2f36fc&lt;SEP&gt;b603e4fb-1b99-49a2-b06a-0160ff173be3</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863737</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Pydantic">
  <data key="d0">Pydantic</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Pydantic is a data parsing and validation library with Python.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0b9224c433c7a1dffba033eb8ed5c941</data>
  <data key="d4">82ac66a6-7ad1-4828-936f-0374dc2f36fc</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863203</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Asyncpg">
  <data key="d0">Asyncpg</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">Asyncpg is a database interface library designed for efficient interaction with PostgreSQL.&lt;SEP&gt;Asyncpg is used with PostgreSQL to provide asynchronous programming capabilities for database operations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0b9224c433c7a1dffba033eb8ed5c941&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-69b74b852f9cabc07d214d1a2ef1a1b7</data>
  <data key="d4">82ac66a6-7ad1-4828-936f-0374dc2f36fc&lt;SEP&gt;b603e4fb-1b99-49a2-b06a-0160ff173be3</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863740</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="OpenAI">
  <data key="d0">OpenAI</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">OpenAI develops artificial intelligence tools and solutions.&lt;SEP&gt;OpenAI is the provider of embedding and generation models used for semantic search and generating answers.&lt;SEP&gt;OpenAI provides the text embedding models used for embeddings creation within Portfolio Vault RAG.&lt;SEP&gt;OpenAI provides the usage.total_tokens data for computing embedding costs.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0b9224c433c7a1dffba033eb8ed5c941&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-69b74b852f9cabc07d214d1a2ef1a1b7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d8787c2876f2fa9c466edf1494e57b95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9b2357e61536898e16b9f8b1b5949ab3</data>
  <data key="d4">82ac66a6-7ad1-4828-936f-0374dc2f36fc&lt;SEP&gt;b603e4fb-1b99-49a2-b06a-0160ff173be3</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863743</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cryptography">
  <data key="d0">Cryptography</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Cryptography is a package designed to expose cryptographic recipes and primitives with Python.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0b9224c433c7a1dffba033eb8ed5c941</data>
  <data key="d4">82ac66a6-7ad1-4828-936f-0374dc2f36fc</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863212</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Python-Docx">
  <data key="d0">Python-Docx</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Python-Docx is a library for creating and updating Microsoft Word (.docx) files with Python.&lt;SEP&gt;Python-Docx is a library required for exporting markdown to .docx format.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0b9224c433c7a1dffba033eb8ed5c941&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9b2357e61536898e16b9f8b1b5949ab3</data>
  <data key="d4">82ac66a6-7ad1-4828-936f-0374dc2f36fc&lt;SEP&gt;b603e4fb-1b99-49a2-b06a-0160ff173be3</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863815</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Markdown">
  <data key="d0">Markdown</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Markdown is a lightweight markup language used to format plain text.&lt;SEP&gt;Markdown is used as the source format for conversion to .docx or .pdf documents.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0b9224c433c7a1dffba033eb8ed5c941&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9b2357e61536898e16b9f8b1b5949ab3</data>
  <data key="d4">82ac66a6-7ad1-4828-936f-0374dc2f36fc&lt;SEP&gt;b603e4fb-1b99-49a2-b06a-0160ff173be3</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863815</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="WeasyPrint">
  <data key="d0">WeasyPrint</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">WeasyPrint is a tool for rendering HTML and CSS documents into PDF format, not installed in Vercel's Lambda environment due to dependencies.&lt;SEP&gt;WeasyPrint is used for converting markdown content to .pdf format.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0b9224c433c7a1dffba033eb8ed5c941&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9b2357e61536898e16b9f8b1b5949ab3</data>
  <data key="d4">82ac66a6-7ad1-4828-936f-0374dc2f36fc&lt;SEP&gt;b603e4fb-1b99-49a2-b06a-0160ff173be3</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863815</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Vercel's Lambda Environment">
  <data key="d0">Vercel's Lambda Environment</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Vercel's Lambda Environment is the serverless computing platform used by Vercel.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0b9224c433c7a1dffba033eb8ed5c941</data>
  <data key="d4">82ac66a6-7ad1-4828-936f-0374dc2f36fc</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863214</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="HTTP 503">
  <data key="d0">HTTP 503</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">HTTP 503 is a status code indicating that the server is not ready to handle the request, often due to maintenance or overload.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0b9224c433c7a1dffba033eb8ed5c941</data>
  <data key="d4">82ac66a6-7ad1-4828-936f-0374dc2f36fc</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863214</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Parallelize Intent Classification And Retrieval">
  <data key="d0">Parallelize Intent Classification And Retrieval</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Intent classification and RAG retrieval are run concurrently using asyncio.create_task to save time on retrieval-heavy turns.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">6caacd2a-0372-40bf-bd0c-0c529eaaee62</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863688</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Llm Model Max Async">
  <data key="d0">Llm Model Max Async</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Llm_model_max_async is a setting increased to 4 to improve concurrent LLM calls within a single query, reducing latency.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">6caacd2a-0372-40bf-bd0c-0c529eaaee62</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863688</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Separate Web And Worker Processes">
  <data key="d0">Separate Web And Worker Processes</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Separate processing for web requests and LightRAG ingestion jobs prevents delays in request handling.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">6caacd2a-0372-40bf-bd0c-0c529eaaee62</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863691</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="LightRAG Local Query Mode">
  <data key="d0">LightRAG Local Query Mode</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">LightRAG is restricted to local entity-focused retrieval, skipping global summary traversal for faster responses to specific questions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">6caacd2a-0372-40bf-bd0c-0c529eaaee62</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863692</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="LightRAG Warm-Up">
  <data key="d0">LightRAG Warm-Up</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Keeping the LightRAG instance warm reduces initial latency by ensuring readiness before user requests.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">6caacd2a-0372-40bf-bd0c-0c529eaaee62</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863694</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Speculative Streaming">
  <data key="d0">Speculative Streaming</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Speculative streaming involves starting LLM token streaming during context resolution to improve perceived response times.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">6caacd2a-0372-40bf-bd0c-0c529eaaee62</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863694</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Intent Caching">
  <data key="d0">Intent Caching</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Intent caching involves short-circuiting classification for short follow-up messages, assuming the intent is refinement.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">6caacd2a-0372-40bf-bd0c-0c529eaaee62</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863694</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Qdrant N Results Tuning">
  <data key="d0">Qdrant N Results Tuning</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Tuning the number of results from Qdrant can optimize the trade-off between speed and response accuracy.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">6caacd2a-0372-40bf-bd0c-0c529eaaee62</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863694</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Connection Pool Sizing">
  <data key="d0">Connection Pool Sizing</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Adjusting connection pool size based on load helps maintain optimal performance and prevent latency issues.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">6caacd2a-0372-40bf-bd0c-0c529eaaee62</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863694</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Response Streaming">
  <data key="d0">Response Streaming</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Response streaming refers to the process of streaming tokens to the browser as they are received from the language model.&lt;SEP&gt;Tokens are streamed to browsers as they are received from the LLM, affecting perceived response latency.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dcd6b1fd8f26bb84cb9d480ce1372752</data>
  <data key="d4">6caacd2a-0372-40bf-bd0c-0c529eaaee62</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863695</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Domain Services Chat File">
  <data key="d0">Domain Services Chat File</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The Domain Services Chat File is a source file associated with the implementation of parallelized intent classification and retrieval.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">6caacd2a-0372-40bf-bd0c-0c529eaaee62</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863702</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Chat Pipeline File">
  <data key="d0">Chat Pipeline File</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The Chat Pipeline File is a source file that involves implementing the LightRAG query mode changes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">6caacd2a-0372-40bf-bd0c-0c529eaaee62</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863703</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Domain Services Lightrag Service File">
  <data key="d0">Domain Services Lightrag Service File</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The Domain Services Lightrag Service File is related to the configuration of the llm model max async setting.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">6caacd2a-0372-40bf-bd0c-0c529eaaee62</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863704</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Build Event Stream">
  <data key="d0">Build Event Stream</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Build Event Stream is a method where the intent caching for short follow-ups would be implemented.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">6caacd2a-0372-40bf-bd0c-0c529eaaee62</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863704</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Render/Railway Free Tier">
  <data key="d0">Render/Railway Free Tier</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Render/Railway Free Tier is a hosting service configuration mentioned in relation to LightRAG warm-up strategies.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">6caacd2a-0372-40bf-bd0c-0c529eaaee62</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863705</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Open Db Engine">
  <data key="d0">Open Db Engine</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Open Db Engine is a method that initializes the database engine, associated with connection pool sizing and keeping LightRAG instances warm.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">6caacd2a-0372-40bf-bd0c-0c529eaaee62</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863705</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Request">
  <data key="d0">Request</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A request is a process that holds a connection for fetching history and persisting messages.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-dcd6b1fd8f26bb84cb9d480ce1372752</data>
  <data key="d4">6caacd2a-0372-40bf-bd0c-0c529eaaee62</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863705</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Pool Size">
  <data key="d0">Pool Size</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Pool size refers to the number of connections available for handling requests, which can be adjusted to manage latency under load.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-dcd6b1fd8f26bb84cb9d480ce1372752</data>
  <data key="d4">6caacd2a-0372-40bf-bd0c-0c529eaaee62</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863705</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Pool Timeout">
  <data key="d0">Pool Timeout</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Pool timeout errors are logged signals indicating issues with connection timing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-dcd6b1fd8f26bb84cb9d480ce1372752</data>
  <data key="d4">6caacd2a-0372-40bf-bd0c-0c529eaaee62</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863712</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="LLM">
  <data key="d0">LLM</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">LLM stands for "Language Learning Model," which processes and retrieves tokens for streaming.&lt;SEP&gt;LLM (Large Language Model) is used in Portfolio Vault RAG for generating conversational knowledge base responses based on markdown vault documents.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-dcd6b1fd8f26bb84cb9d480ce1372752&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-69b74b852f9cabc07d214d1a2ef1a1b7</data>
  <data key="d4">6caacd2a-0372-40bf-bd0c-0c529eaaee62&lt;SEP&gt;b603e4fb-1b99-49a2-b06a-0160ff173be3</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863773</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Time-To-First-Token (TTFT)">
  <data key="d0">Time-To-First-Token (TTFT)</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">TTFT represents the latency between the initiation of a request and the arrival of the first streaming token in the browser.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-dcd6b1fd8f26bb84cb9d480ce1372752</data>
  <data key="d4">6caacd2a-0372-40bf-bd0c-0c529eaaee62</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863715</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Latency">
  <data key="d0">Latency</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Latency refers to the delay before a transfer of data begins following an instruction for its transfer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-dcd6b1fd8f26bb84cb9d480ce1372752</data>
  <data key="d4">6caacd2a-0372-40bf-bd0c-0c529eaaee62</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863715</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Portfolio Vault RAG">
  <data key="d0">Portfolio Vault RAG</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Portfolio Vault RAG is a Python server using FastAPI backend that transforms markdown vault documents into a searchable knowledge base.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-69b74b852f9cabc07d214d1a2ef1a1b7</data>
  <data key="d4">b603e4fb-1b99-49a2-b06a-0160ff173be3</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863737</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Qdrant">
  <data key="d0">Qdrant</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">Qdrant is an organization providing a service for vector storage and search, used to upsert vectors in the described index pipeline.&lt;SEP&gt;Qdrant is used as the Vector Database for local or cloud storage solutions in Portfolio Vault RAG.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-69b74b852f9cabc07d214d1a2ef1a1b7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d8787c2876f2fa9c466edf1494e57b95</data>
  <data key="d4">b603e4fb-1b99-49a2-b06a-0160ff173be3</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863737</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="PostgreSQL">
  <data key="d0">PostgreSQL</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">PostgreSQL is a Relational Database Management System used in Portfolio Vault RAG alongside SQLModel and asyncpg.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-69b74b852f9cabc07d214d1a2ef1a1b7</data>
  <data key="d4">b603e4fb-1b99-49a2-b06a-0160ff173be3</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863753</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Anthropic Claude">
  <data key="d0">Anthropic Claude</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">Anthropic Claude is an optional generation model used for generating answers in Portfolio Vault RAG.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-69b74b852f9cabc07d214d1a2ef1a1b7</data>
  <data key="d4">b603e4fb-1b99-49a2-b06a-0160ff173be3</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863755</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Fernet">
  <data key="d0">Fernet</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">Fernet is a method using AES-128-CBC with HMAC encryption for securely storing API keys.&lt;SEP&gt;Fernet symmetric encryption is used for API key encryption within Portfolio Vault RAG using 'cryptography'.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-69b74b852f9cabc07d214d1a2ef1a1b7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d8787c2876f2fa9c466edf1494e57b95</data>
  <data key="d4">b603e4fb-1b99-49a2-b06a-0160ff173be3</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863755</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="OpenAI GPT">
  <data key="d0">OpenAI GPT</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">OpenAI GPT is an optional generation model used in Portfolio Vault RAG for generating answers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-69b74b852f9cabc07d214d1a2ef1a1b7</data>
  <data key="d4">b603e4fb-1b99-49a2-b06a-0160ff173be3</data>
  <data key="d5">1773863755</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="SQLModel Table Definitions">
  <data key="d0">SQLModel Table Definitions</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">SQLModel Table Definitions refers to the files in ``models/`` which include VaultDocument, PipelineRun, AppSetting, and QueryLog.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-69b74b852f9cabc07d214d1a2ef1a1b7</data>
  <data key="d4">b603e4fb-1b99-49a2-b06a-0160ff173be3</data>
